                          Sept. 21 (Bloomberg) -- Lakshman Achuthan, managing director of the  Economic Cycle Research Institute in New York, talks about the outlook for the U.S. economy.
     The worst U.S. recession since the Great Depression ended in June 2009, the National Bureau of Economic Research said yesterday, as a slowdown in economic growth raises the possibility of another slump. Achuthan talks with Susan Li on Bloomberg Television's "First Up."  (Source: Bloomberg)  
                   
    

                 
           
                           
                 
                 
                                       
                                   
               
                        
           
                          Sept. 21 (Bloomberg) -- Larry Kantor, head of research at Barclays Capital in New York, talks about the outlook for the U.S. economy and stocks.
     The worst U.S. recession since the Great Depression ended in June 2009, the National Bureau of Economic Research said yesterday, as a slowdown in economic growth raises the possibility of another slump. The decision came as Federal Reserve policy makers meet this week to consider whether new measures to boost growth are needed and the Obama administration proposes additional fiscal stimulus. Kantor talks with Susan Li on Bloomberg Television's "First Up." (Source: Bloomberg)  
                           

     
